org.anchoranalysis.plugin.image.task.bean.segment

Class SegmentInstanceWithModel<T>

  • Object
    • AnchorBean<Task<T,S>>
      • Task<StackSequenceInput,SharedStateSegmentInstance<T>>
        • SegmentInstanceWithModel<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - model-type in pool

    public class SegmentInstanceWithModel<T>
extends Task<StackSequenceInput,SharedStateSegmentInstance<T>>
    Using a model-pool, performs instance segmentation on an image producing zero, one or more objects per image.

    Various visualizations and export types are supported.

    The task will output the segmentation results (in HDF5 form and as a mask) for each input, together with visualizations of the outlines.

    The task also provides aggregated outputs (features, thumbnails) of extracted objects across all inputs.

    The following outputs are produced:

    Output NameDefault?Description
    inputnoThe input image for segmentation.
    objectsyesSegmented object-masks encoded into HDF5.
    maskyesA binary-mask image that binary ors each voxel across the segmented object-masks.
    outlineyesA RGB image showing the outline of segmented-objects on top of the input image.
    summaryyesA CSV file showing basic feature of all segmented-objects across all input images.
    thumbnailsyesA directory of thumbnails showing the outline of all segmented objects on top of an extracted portion of the respective input-image.
